Awesome! My favorite subject in school was science!
History is one my favorites as well!

I really enjoyed history too. But science was always intriguing to me.
Especially when the two intersect, like with paleontology.

Agreed. I actually wanted to be a paleontologist as a kid as a matter of fact.
Some of the first Trex fossils were found in Montana and Wyoming in the early 1900's.  I'd really like to go on a dinosaur dig one day.

Same here. I've actually found fossilized dino poop on a dig for native American artifacts once.
That is quite an odd find.  Where were you at?

Somewhere in south Alabama, roughly 20 miles north of the Alabama coast. A lot of artifacts in that area.
I will have to look into that.  I had no idea!

It's a hotbed. My dad and I would dig all over Alabama and Georgia as a kid. Need to visit again soon!
That sounds like an awesome memory to have together.

"I don't work. I am a full time buddhist. So I meditate 10 hours every day"
"how do you pay bills? I couldn't survive without my job"

"It help. Consumerism is detrimental to human life. You don't need a lot to live a worthful life."
"wow thats interesting. I don't think i could do that, I have a big family"

"On donation. Its not a lot, but I don't need a lot. I only eat rice with vegetables and drink only water to purify my body."
"Can't do that lol I love meat too much. I am an avid hunter, and fisherman. I live off what I harvest. "

"I understand its not for everyone. If you are interested, you can start by being vegan. Its a good step in the right direction"
"I understand and I respect that"

"Its another way of living life. We believe in reincarnation so for me, all animals are sacred."
"3 girls I also have 3 cats and 2 dogs"

"I'm only 18 and I still live at home."
"DO you live in an urban area or closer to nature?"

"The burbs. But there's woods behind the house."
"There is a lot of math found in nature. Are you familiar with the Fibonacci Sequence?"

"No. What's that?"
"The Fibonacci sequence is one of the most famous formulas in mathematics. Each number in the sequence is the sum of the two numbers that precede it."

"Isn't that like a spiral or something to do with shells?"
"Yes, the swirls, also known as the "Golden Ratio" found throughout nature."

"I heard about that in a science class, I think. Kind of over my head, though."
"I disliked math class myself but am intrigued how it applies to our natural world.  After all, math IS just a theory."

I have two older half brothers, one younger half brother, and a younger half sister. I have three older siblings. Do you wish you were an only child?
Well I consider myself an only child actually, because I never lived with my siblings. I hated it to be honest. It was lonely. Your parents should have gotten you a pet. I had a dog and it was wonderful.
Fortunately we almost always had a dog. That did help a lot for sure. I began working online as a side gig recently and my dog keeps me company. That's great, what kind of side gig? I'm doing something similar right now.
I have two actually. One of them I go places, take pictures, and answer questions. I eat meat so it's good they have pizza mystery shopping. That sounds fun. Does it pay well?
Certain ones really do. It follows your location if you want it too, so when traveling, I do jobs along the way and pay for gas or the trip itself! How nice. I could use some supplemental income.
Can't we all. I know it definitely helps support my family, especially while my wife is out of work. You sound like a real stand-up guy.

"Not really.  I find it hard to relate to people." 
"You are not a social type of person?"
"How so?"
"I am in a wheel chair, so they help me get around town."
"Oh yes, I'm sure they are very helpful right now.  Someday I will probably wish I got along with people better than animals."
"Yes they are sometime, but they are useful right now."
"It's just so hard to find a place to meet new people."
"Some people are pretty cool when you start knowing them."
"That's a good idea. I enjoy photographing animals, what are your hobbies?"
"Think of your favorite hobby, and find a group interested in the same hobby as you in your city. Thats the best way."
"I watch birds around my house and do some gardening."

column3:
Some mornings my cat is on the bed, a little bundle of heat next to me.
My cat is usually sleeping on top of me in the morning.  I am always trying to move him without waking him up.

I do that also, but then he decides he wants his breakfast, and then it's hard to ignore him.
Mine is the same and he asks loudly!

And then after he eats, he can spend the rest of the day sleeping.  But I have to stay up and go to work.
I am retired, and if I sit down for even a minute my cat is in my lap.  He can be a nuisance.

Maybe offices would be more fun if we had cats at our desks.
That I totally agree with, there is something soothing and comforting about hearing a cat purring.

I think retirement will be better than working in many respects, not just cat availability.
I love retirement.  How far from retirement are you?

Hopefully just a few years. I think about it a lot!
Well I think the secret to a happy retirement is to find something you like to do.  Sitting around can get very boring, stay busy.

I eat a lot of noodles. I like to add cheese and meat when possible. Where do you work?
work in the library at the small community college I attend. it doesn't pay that great but I have access to the material for school. how about you?

I help my grandma she makes jewelry. I sell it online.
sounds like she keeps busy. do you help with making the jewelry, as well? do you sell on sites like craigslist or do you have your own webpage?

Yes. It is fun . a lot on ebay.
that's a way to make a buck! Ebay's a great place to get an idea about prices.  It is a multinational e-commerce corporation. go you entrepreneur!

Thanks. Do you have any hobbies?
well, I've gotten so many ideas from this site. small hobbies that can go big. A cake baker, investing, and now jewelry making... wow. hobbies. who knew?

Funny, I wish I was better at saving and investing. Do you like your school?
That's inspirational at least. I'm sure we can all do better at saving. School is.. an experience that I'm appreciative of. It's a step to the next level.

I hear you. School is stressful sometimes. What did you eat today?
nothing healthy! :-) basically ramen chicken flavored. and coffee! what a combination. haha now that I see it in writing. will do better. :-D

"It helps you create JavaScript applications. We use it at the school where I'm a teacher."

"I enjoy creating websites but havent heard about it"
"It is pretty easy to use, you should look into it! Do you create websites for work?"

"No, I do them for myself"
"Oh, nice! I've been wanting to build my own website, but I've been going through a hard time and it's taking all my energy."

"I've been doing a lot of things for myself lately. I want to start investing money"
"Really, what is a good place to invest money?"

"I don't know. I just started to do some research"
"Well, I guess I have plenty of time to do my own research, now that I'm single. I wish you luck in your investments! "

"Thank you. Good luck to you too."
"Thank you, maybe I can focus on doing something with art since that's what I teach! My future is looking bright!"

column3:
He was in the military when I was in the 70s.
"It's so nice to talk to someone who knew my dad! So I guess you guys fought side by side in the war?"

We fought side by side and we ate side by side. Only red meat of course! We were good friends.
"Haha, well I'm a vegetarian so I guess I didn't get that from him. I love mushrooms and pasta, especially ravioli! What was his job in the military?"

Military police. He commanded the 110th division. Great man.
"Well, that's something we have in common! I have always had a desire to be a police officer."

Have you taken steps to acheive this dream?
"I was a junior police officer when I was a teenager and it was great! Since then I've been scared to take the leap!"

Thats too bad. You should always chase the dreams of your youth.

column3:
"I've heard of it.. I actually was held hostage once during a store robbery."
"Oh wow, I am glad you are okay. Nothing you can do to avoid it in public but I have a dog for home protection."

"I don't have a dog right now.. but we had one growing up.. my dad wasn't home much as he was a cop at the time."
"I am always home baking and cooking. I would worry about a family member having such a dangerous job."

"Well he's retired now.. so fortunately it worked out ok for him :)  I love to cook, but I'm not a very good baker :)"
"Aww good, I bet he enjoys retirement. That move Hostage showed how important a cops job is."

"Yeah it did.. it was actually fairly accurate, too.  Law Enforcement, in general, go through a LOT of turmoil in their lives."
"I have to most respect for them because they have to deal with extreme mental stress."

"Absolutely.. not a lot of jobs out there where you are literally unsure if you're going to be returning home alive at the end of the day."
"That would definitely be a job I would not want, but we need heroes to stop bad people like in Hostle."

"With the way the world is, yes, we always need Heroes :)"
"I would hate to imagine the world without people to protect us from the crazy's in the world today."

'Well I was born in Spain, but when I was 12 my family moved to Illinoise work better work opportunities. '

column3:
I keep it at a boatyard. I have my own boat too, it makes it possible to fish for snowcrab. 
"That's nice! I've been wanting to start oystering, but I'm have a baby, for the second time around. I don't think a boat would be my friend."

Oh my word! Congratulations! I eat a lot of oysters, I love eating all sorts of seafood. 
"Thank you, we're getting excited! I am a vegetarian who only eats oysters. That seems funny when I say it out loud!"

Ha ha! People that only eat fish meat are called pescatarians. But does that include oysters? I am not sure. 
"Lol, I'm not sure either! Labels can be confusing. I'm an artist so I just try to roll with it:)"

Wow, what kind of artist are you? I love to paint fish and the sea but I am not so skilled. 
"I am a photographer, my mentor is Sally Mann! Most of my pieces are on landscapes and people, the capturing of the soul. I love that you paint!"

Oh, a photographer, I see. I am not familiar with Sally Mann unfortunately. I will look for her instagram. But yes, I love to finger paint, it relaxes me.
"Yes, do look into her, you won't regret it. Wow! Finger painting, now that's a technique I haven't thought about for quite some time! So cool:)"

I will have to try to remember my instagram password, haha! Yes, I love to finger paint, and do full body paintings, but it uses a lot of paint.
"Totally, we have too many passwords to remember!! How much does it cost you to do a full body painting?"

I am unsure, normally I would use up 1 bucket of paint. But taking a bath afterwards is terribly messy. 
"Hahahaha! I bet:) Sorry to have to leave so soon, but my oldest child is yelling for lunch! It's been great chatting with you, hope to do it again soon!"
column4:
من آن را در کشتی‌سازی نگه می‌دارم. من هم یک قایق خود دارم، این امکان را فراهم می‌کند که برای شکم‌پر اسنوکرب ماهیگیری کنم.

ای وای! تبریک میگم! من خیلی صدف میخورم، عاشق خوردن انواع ماهی و دریایی ها هستم.

ههه! افرادی که فقط گوشت ماهی می‌خورند، با نام پسکاتاریان شناخته می‌شوند. اما آیا این شامل صدف‌ها هم می‌شود؟ من مطمئن نیستم.

وای، چه نوع هنرمندی هستید؟ من عاشق نقاشی ماهی و دریا هستم اما مهارت زیادی ندارم.

اوه، یک عکاس، می‌بینم. متاسفانه با سالی من آشنا نیستم. من قصد دارم اینستاگرام او را بیابم. اما بله، من عاشق نقاشی با انگشت هستم، این من را آرام می‌کند.

باید سعی کنم رمز عبور اینستاگرامم را به یاد بیاورم، هاها! بله، من عاشق نقاشی انگشت هستم و نقاشی بدن کامل انجام می دهم، اما از رنگ زیادی استفاده می کند.

مطمئن نیستم، معمولاً یک سطل رنگ مصرف می‌کنم. اما بعداز آن حمام گرفتن بسیار کثیف است.
column5:
این خوبه! من می‌خواستم شروع به جمع آوری صدف کنم، اما من یک بچه دارم، برای دومین بار. فکر نمی‌کنم که قایق دوست من باشد.

I love gardening, what kind of plants do you plan to plant? I want to keep it low maintenance, so that I have time to go to the beach as well, which is nearby
Understandable. I'd recommend just evergreens then. I wish i lived near the beach. Good idea ! I think I'll need to do some research into conditions and soil before buying. Do you surf ?
No, but I love the ocean and spending time with family and friends there. I do paddle bard when I'm off work, and I hope my new house is fully decorated so I don't need to miss too many summer days.
I tried paddle boarding once. It was a disaster, fell right off. When do you hope to move in? In 6 weeks - fingers crossed. Yes, it takes time to learn, but great fun once you have. Do you go to family beaches ?
Yes, most of the time. How about you? No not really as I'm single. Its been so hot this year hasn't it...
Yes. Really out of the norm. The beach is a great place to meet other single people, have you had any luck? Sadly, no, but I'm always on the look-out.....met lots of nice people and made friends though. I'm wondering about getting A/C installed, have you got it ?

'That sounds like a great idea. Can you tell me more about Goodwill Industries?'
'Goodwill Industries help hire other who may lack education or face employment challenges. It helps them with work skills in that way.'

'Thats incredible! I am looking for a job at the moment. I recently finished up a six month contract as a broadway style dancer on a cruise ship.'
"How exciting! I've never been on a cruise. Where did you sail?"

'The cruise ship I worked on went to Jamacia, Mexico and the Cayman Islands. I would highly recommend cruising.'
"Maybe I'll look into some cruises in the Pacific. It's a good thing I live along the coast."

'You should. What do you do for work?'
'I freelance, but when I can, I do volunteer work with an organization that donates tools to families and communities in Africa.'

'Thats really neat! How did you get involved with the volunteer work?'
'I shop at Goodwill a lot and connected with a group that volunteers there.'

column3:
Roller coasters let you see the trees from a different perspective, when you are at the very top
So true! Plus you're able to see the world from a perspective you've never seen. You ever been to Disney World?

Only once, many years ago.  I was just a child.
My mother took me a lot as a kid. My dad left when I was only 5, so she took me there to get my mind off of it.

It's good to be able to lose yourself in an activity you love.  For me now, that is painting.
Agreed. I wish I was talented enough to paint. Do you ever paint any rollercoaster portraits?

No, I never have.  I can visualize one peeking out over the trees from a distance though.  Joins nature and civilization in a whimsical way.
I bet your portraits are amazing! I get as much of a thrill out of nature as I do rollercoasters.

I wish I lived near the mountains...so much more variety in nature. But I have learned to find the beauty of the plains.
You should look into Tennessee. The mountains there are majestic - plus they have plenty of amusement parks in the mountains for people like me.

Then I could visit Dollywood!
Also, Ashville, North Carolina is great. The Bitmore is a mansion located in Asheville that is begging for a portrait. Ha!

فقط یک برابر، سال‌ها پیش. من فقط یک کودک بودم.

خوب است که بتوانید خود را در یک فعالیتی که دوست دارید گم کنید. برای من در حال حاضر، این نقاشی است.

نه، هرگز نداشته‌ام. اما می‌توانم تصور کنم که یکی از آنها از دور بیرون از درختان نگاه می‌کند. به طرزی شگفت‌انگیز طبیعت و تمدن را ترکیب می‌کند.

می‌خواستم کنار کوه‌ها زندگی می‌کردم... طبیعت بسیار متنوع‌تری دارند. اما من یاد گرفته‌ام زیبایی دشت‌ها را پیدا کنم.

سپس می‌توانستم به دالوود بروم!

مادرم زمانی که من کودک بودم، من را بسیار برد. پدرم زمانی که من فقط 5 ساله بودم رفت، بنابراین او من را به آنجا برد تا ذهنم از این موضوع دور شود.

column3:
"She's a few months old. I am Mary from Colorado. What is your name?"
"Jeff, actually in the UK so a good distance from you. ;o) I would love a dog, I think it might make me exercise more"

"Awww wow you are a distance a way lol. Exercise is great I enjoy hiking in the summer. What do you prefer?"
"Well, I don't really know what I prefer yet as I'm just starting a health drive - after giving up smoking recently"

"Oh wow, that is amazing. Congratulations on your continued health journey. Quiting anything can be really hard."
"Thanks, I am rather proud as it was tough. What do you do in the winter though, if you hike in the summer only ?"

"You're very welcome. I like to go skiing in the mountains and relax at my cabin by a nice fire with a cup of hot cocoa."
"OOoooo that sounds idyllic. I wonder if I could persuade my friends to go with me to do that? I go on holidays with them, but have never tried skiiing."

"Yessss, persuade them to do so lol it is amazing. We only get one life so we might as well enjoy it, right?"
"Even if a leg or two gets broken - yes lol Can you take your puppy/dog with you to the lodge ?"

"Lol that is funny, yes I can take her and she enjoys it too. I buy the cute little coat and shoes for her to run around in the snow."
"Oh I've seen those dog snow boots, they are adorable. I'm back to wanting a dog.......lol"
column4:
او چند ماهه است. من مری از کلرادو هستم. نام شما چیست؟

"اووواااااااااااااااااااااااااااااااااااااااااااااااااااااااااااااااااااااااااااااااااااااااااااااااااا

"واو، این عالیه. تبریک میگم بهت برای سفر سلامتی پیوسته‌ات. ترک کردن هر چیزی میتونه خیلی سخت باشه."

خواهش می‌کنم. من دوست دارم در کوه‌ها اسکی کنم و در کلبه‌ام کنار آتش خوبی با یک فنجان کاکائو گرم استراحت کنم.

بله، آنها را متقاعد کنید که این کار را انجام دهند هاها این عالی است. ما فقط یک بار زندگی می‌کنیم، پس بهتر است از آن لذت ببریم، درست است؟

ههه این خنده داره، بله من می‌تونم اون رو ببرم و اون هم لذت می‌بره. یک کت و کفش کوچولو و زیبا برای اون می‌خرم تا در برف بدونه.
column5:
جف، در واقع در انگلستان هستم، بنابراین فاصله خوبی از شما دارم. دوست دارم یک سگ داشته باشم، فکر می‌کنم ممکن است باعث شود من بیشتر ورزش کنم.

خب، واقعا هنوز نمی دانم که چه چیزی را ترجیح می دهم زیرا که تازه شروع به تلاش برای حفظ سلامتی کرده ام - پس از ترک سیگار اخیرا"

ممنونم، خیلی خودم رو به خاطر این افتخار می‌کنم چون خیلی سخت بود. اما تو زمستان چه کاری می‌کنی اگر تنها تابستانه پیاده‌روی می‌کنی؟

اوووووو این خیلی زیبا به نظر می‌رسه. من تعجب می‌کنم که آیا می‌تونم دوستام رو متقاعد کنم که با من برن تا این کارو انجام بدیم؟ من با اونها سفرهای تعطیلاتی می‌رم، اما هیچ وقت اسکی امتحان نکردم.

حتی اگر یک یا دو پا شکسته شود - بله ههه آیا می‌توانید سگ کوچکتان را با خود به کلبه ببرید؟

اوه، من اون بوت های برفی برای سگ ها رو دیدم، خیلی جذابن. دوباره دلم برای یک سگ تنگ شده.......هههه

همه دوست دارند نتفلیکس ببینند، من اخیراً مایندهانتر را دیدم، شما؟ من عاشق بازی فوتبال هستم، بنابراین بسیاری از بازیکنان معروف فوتبال را می کشم. من اخیراً این برنامه به نام هانتد را دیدم که مردم درباره تجربیات خود با پدیده های ماورایی صحبت می کنند. واقعاً جالب است.

'It is a composite of the many skills required for putting on a show.'
'oh wow! that sounds interesting! last time I took a test I was almost late as my car broke down!   '
'Wow almost a bummer. I get confused between my studying for the test and for my show sometimes.'
'Yeah I got an old car from my dad that kept breaking down when I was in college! Are you singing in the show?'
'Why yes as well as dancing too. Do you have a better car now?'
"That sounds fun! I used to do a bit of musical performance when I was younger. I have the same car actually but I don't drive as often now."

'Next week!'
'Good luck in your studying! what is the test on?'
"Oh, I drive a lot to put on my show and the hamburgers I eat keep me going. Are you living in a city then with mass transit?"
"I also love hamburgers, I probably eat far too much lol. Yeah I use buses and trams to get around now mainly."
"I live too far out of the city to use a bus. Isn't a hamburger a complete meal with tomato and lettuce?"
'Yeah, but you can add other ingredients too, my favourite is cheese and bacon. Do you like pizza? I just found a great place near me that does amazing pizzas.'

"I can only imagine. How old is your Mom? "

"That's horrible, my Mom is pushing 70 and went to Florida because that's where old people go."
"Is she still in good health?"
"for the most part, she used to smoke and she has bad teeth that will eventually need to come out "
"I'm sorry to hear that- dental work is so expensive in the US."
"What's it like to not almost die from eating apples?"
"I don't really like them much anyway. My mom does though, so I keep them in the house."

"I'm in medical school as well so I know how long the hours can be."
"What field of medicine are you studying?"

"Pediatrics. But I also love theater as well and I do community theater on the side."
"Ah cool! So you'll deal with children from birth through adolescence?"

"Basically. Anything to help kids and their diseases. I feel as if that's my 'calling'."
"Was there anything that made you want to become a pediatrician?"

"Well, I love kids and I was inspired by my own pediatrician as a kid. He was my role model growing up."
"That is really cool. how many years of school have you went through so far?"

"Only one thus far so I have a long road ahead of me to say the least. lol I'm at the University of Cincinnati."
"aaaah, but it will all be worth it in the long run!"

"So true! But if all else fails, I do enjoy theater work as well so theater is always an option. Ha!"
"Were you forced to go into medical school? It seems you really want to go into theater"

"Nah, I chose medical school as a career and theater is just sort of a hobby, ya know?"
"being a doctor will be more rewarding I think. Maybe you can still act as a hobby"

column3:
"It absolutely is and I love watching Grey's Anatomy. How about you?"
"I do. Most would probably think I'm strange cause I know so much about the show, along with that I have orange and blue hair lol."

"Lol that is funny. I can't live with out it honestly it's apart of my every day life. I live by a schedule to stay sane lol."
"I would like to live more by a set schedule, but my 3-year-old makes that difficult lol"

"Lol I can really relate kids are adorable and they definitely keep you on your toes."
"That they do. I'm enjoying my daughter and hoping to have one more child in the next couple of years. I dread their teenage years though."

"I can say the teenage years are scary let me tell you"
"Oh I'm sure. They were scary enough for me when I was a teenager. Things are so different these days from 20 years ago!"

"Yes it is and it's so sad to say the least"
"That it is. We spent most of our time outdoors and now they all live in their phones moreso than anywhere else. Sigh."

"Ugh. I completely agree and just think Grey's Anatomy will be a thing of the past."
"I dread the day when it is. Hopefully Netflix and other outlets like cable TV will keep it alive like they did some other shows like The Andy Griffith Show."

"Yes good ole Netflix is the best. I really enjoyed our conversation."
"I did as well. Thank you."

این قطعاً درست است و من دوست دارم سریال گریز آناتومی را تماشا کنم. شما چطور؟

ههه این خنده داره. راستش نمی‌تونم بدون اون زندگی کنم، واقعاً جزئی از زندگی روزمره‌امه. برای حفظ عقلم به یک برنامه زندگی می‌کنم ههه.

ههه من واقعا میتونم ارتباط بگیرم، بچه ها خیلی جذابن و قطعا تو راه میان.

می‌توانم بگویم که سال‌های نوجوانی ترسناک هستند، اجازه بدهید به شما بگویم.

بله، واقعاً افسوس‌آور است که بگویم کمترین اندازه‌ای از آن است.

اوف. کاملاً موافقم و فکر می‌کنم که گریز آناتومی یک چیزی از گذشته خواهد بود.

"بله نتفلیکس خیلی خوبه. واقعاً از گفتگوی ما لذت بردم."

من انجام می دهم. بیشتر احتمالا فکر می کنند که من عجیب هستم چون خیلی در مورد این برنامه می دانم، همراه با اینکه موهای نارنجی و آبی دارم ههه.

من دوست دارم بیشتر بر اساس یک برنامه زمانی زندگی کنم، اما فرزند سه ساله‌ام این کار را دشوار می‌کند. لول.

آنها این کار را انجام می‌دهند. من از دخترم لذت می‌برم و امیدوارم که در چند سال آینده یک فرزند دیگر داشته باشم. اما از سن نوجوانی آن‌ها می‌ترسم.

اوه مطمئنم. برای من کافی ترسناک بودند وقتی نوجوان بودم. این روزها امور خیلی متفاوت از بیست سال پیش هستند!

اینطور است. بیشتر وقت خود را در فضای باز سپری می‌کردیم و اکنون آن‌ها بیشتر از هر جای دیگری در گوشی‌هایشان زندگی می‌کنند. افسوس.

من از روزی که این اتفاق می افتد می ترسم. امیدوارم Netflix و دیگر وسایل ارتباطی مانند تلویزیون کابلی آن را زنده نگه دارند، همانند برخی برنامه های دیگر مانند برنامه The Andy Griffith Show.

من هم همین کار را کردم. ممنون.

'I have only flown into the Baltimore airport.  I have never spent time in the city.' 
"Baltimore's Inner Harbor is a big tourist attraction. Lots to offer"

"I have been to the Boston harbor but not Baltimore's harbor, maybe it is similar."
'Possibly so. What are you up to?'

"I'm trying to reach something on a high shelf but I'm too short."
"Oh no that's no good grab a chair."

"I would but I'm afraid my dog will knock it over while I'm on it."
"Oh wow what kind of dog do you have? I'm actually looking for dog training jobs right now."

'I have a belgian malinois.'
'I like Belgian Malinois dogs. However, their ancestor species are extinct I hear. Kennel him until you are done with the chair.'

"That's a good idea, I will do that."
'Awesome. What are your plans today?'

That's convenient. Did you know that the word breakfast comes from 'breaking a fast' meaning a fasting period in the middle of the night?
Wow, didn't know that. I just know I love eating eggs for breakfast. LOL
I eat 6 eggs every morning for breakfast. Good source of protein.
That's a lot, good for you. Thanks! Protein is essential for good health. Do you try to eat healthy?

این نژاد فوق‌العاده‌ای است. هر ماه چند کیسه غذای سگ مصرف می‌کنید؟ معمولاً حدود سه کیسه بزرگ مصرف می‌کنیم. همچنین غذای انسانی هم به آن‌ها می‌دهم، عادت بدی می‌دانم.

I enjoy writing childrens books as a hobby and also enjoying drinking goes hand in hand. It makes me more creative lol.
That's when the creative juicy's flow lol. I sometimes do crazy things when I drink like a little late night riding on my mountain bike.

That sounds fun actually! I have to watch myself though, cause if someone gives me bad stimuli while drinking, I can have a bad mouth.
Ooooh yes I agree with you on that. The craziest thing when I drink I crave boiled eggs, so weird.

lol, really? I haven't heard that one before. I crave carbs it seems, like chips or crackers the most, for sure.
Yes, it is soooo weird. Chips sound so good right now lol I swear

Maybe I'll try to center my next book around chip cravings in some way or another! What's your favorite potato chip?
That would be a great one. Oooh that's a great question, at this moment tortilla chips with a hint of jalapeno

I love pickled jalapenos. My favorite chip would be Flamin' Hot Cheetos or the cheese Pringles.
Yes pickled one are amazing and that would be another one of my favorites

If you like tuna, I've found they go GREAT cut up and mixed with that! And I love them on top of nachos too of course.
Yes I love tuna and nachos are great as well. Do you like the mild, medium, or hot?

این واقعاً جالب به نظر می‌رسد! اما باید خودم را زیر نظر داشته باشم، چون اگر کسی در حالی که مشروب می‌نوشم به من تحریک بدی بدهد، ممکن است بدگویی کنم.

شاید سعی کنم کتاب بعدی خود را در مورد تمایلات به چیپ‌ها متمرکز کنم، به یک شکل یا دیگر! چیپ مورد علاقه‌ی شما چیست؟

اگر ماهی تن می‌پسندید، من متوجه شدم که وقتی آنها ریز شده و با هم مخلوط شوند، عالی می‌شوند! و البته من آنها را روی ناچوز هم دوست دارم.

"How many kids do you have?"
"2- but that is a lot, trust me."
"I wouldn't know, I don't have any kids.  Do you have time for yourself with 2 kids?"
"Not really. I used to follow my favorite band's tour, but not anymore. :("
"That's too bad.  I would love to be a band's fashion coordinator.  It would be right up my alley."
'That sounds like fun! I always assumed bands just put on whatever clothes they felt like.'
"That's what they want you to think, but the biggest bands have their outfit coordination down to a science."
'Hmm ,never really thought about it that way. Why do you think that is?'
"I think it's just all about image and what they try to portray.  Are you influenced by the way band's look, or just their music?"
"Their look doesn't matter much to me- I'm all about the music!"
"Who's your favorite band?"
"Queens of the Stone Age- definitely!"

I went surfing for the first time in Tofino, BC last summer. It was a little expensive for lessons, but worth it in the end.
BC? Is that British Columbia?
Yes, have you been around the West Coast at all?
Not yet, but I've been to Canada. How cold was the water when you were surfing there?
It was pretty chilly. I went in the beginning of June, so we had to have full bodysuits, boots included. Couldn't have been more than 12 degrees C.
Sweet. I love to surf, but have only been on the Atlantic side, and once on a trip to Brazil. Some killer waves there.
I actually want to move out of the country eventually. Brazil sounds amazing. I just can't seem to part with Canada just yet. Do you travel a lot?
Brazil is amazing. Yeah, I travel as much as possible. Any cool places in Canada to recommend?

تابستان گذشته برای اولین بار در توفینو، بریتیش کلمبیا موج سواری کردم. هزینه یادگیری کمی گران بود، اما در نهایت ارزشش را داشت.

بله، آیا تا حالا در سواحل غربی حضور داشته‌اید؟

هوا خیلی سرد بود. من در اوایل ژوئن رفتم، بنابراین ما باید لباس‌های کامل بدن داشته باشیم، شامل بوت‌ها. ممکن است بیشتر از ۱۲ درجه سانتیگراد نبود.

من در واقع می‌خواهم در نهایت از کشور خارج شوم. برزیل بسیار جذاب به نظر می‌رسد. فقط به نظر نمی‌رسد که هنوز از کانادا جدا شوم. آیا شما زیاد سفر می‌کنید؟

برزیل شگفت‌انگیز است. آره، من تا جایی که ممکن است سفر می‌کنم. هر مکان جالبی در کانادا برای پیشنهاد دارید؟

column3:
I think I heard of New Found Glory, but not super familiar with them. I started doing work online not long ago. Loving it so far!
That is amazing I love online work and ordering food online lol. Guilty pleasure is Mcdonalds

I love McDonald's also. Me and my family do lots of shopping online but making money online is new territory for us.
I think you will really enjoy it. Do you have a big family?

Nah, just a three person household right now and the family I was born with isn't really large either.
Oh ok I have a really big family. The youngest of eight and my husband I have three kids and twins are baking in the oven lol.

Wow! That sounds more like a huge family lol. Congrats on the upcoming twins! My wife and I plan to have at least one more, two tops.
Thank you, we're really excited and decided to wait to find out what we're having. Kids are amazing aren't they.

Yes they are. It's fun seeing some of your own traits in them and then understanding why your parents yelled at you so much lol.
Omg, it's fun and nerve wrecking at times lol. Now I understand oh so well.

That's why a side job is so important too, to support them more easily lol.
Side JOBS lol woooh they require a lot. As parents we want to make sure they have the best life possible.
column4:
فکر می‌کنم قبلاً از گروه New Found Glory شنیده‌ام، اما خیلی آشنا به آن‌ها نیستم. من اخیراً شروع به کار آنلاین کردم. تا الان خیلی دوست داشتنی بوده است!

من هم عاشق مک‌دونالدز هستم. من و خانواده‌ام بسیار خرید آنلاین انجام می‌دهیم اما کسب درآمد آنلاین برای ما منطقه‌ی جدیدی است.

نه، در حال حاضر فقط یک خانواده سه نفره هستیم و خانواده‌ای که در آن به دنیا آمده‌ام هم واقعا بزرگ نیست.

واو! این بثرت به نظر می‌رسد مثل یک خانواده بزرگه هاهاها. تبریک به مناسبت دوقلوهای آینده! همسرم و من قصد داریم حداقل یک نفر دیگر داشته باشیم، حداکثر دو نفر.

بله، آنها هستند. خوشحالم که ویژگی‌های خودم را در آنها می‌بینم و می‌فهمم چرا پدر و مادرم انقدر به من داد می‌زدند، ههه.

به همین دلیل کار پاره وقت هم خیلی مهم است، تا به راحتی بتوانند بیشتر حمایت شوند هاها.
column5:
این فوق‌العاده است، من عاشق کار آنلاین و سفارش غذا آنلاین هستم هاها. گناهکاری من مک‌دونالدز است.

فکر می‌کنم واقعاً از آن لذت خواهید برد. آیا خانواده‌ی بزرگی دارید؟

اوه، خب من یک خانواده بسیار بزرگ دارم. جوانترین فرزند هشت نفره هستم و شوهرم سه فرزند داریم و دوقلوها در فرن ما در حال پختن هستند هاها.

متشکریم، ما واقعاً هیجان زده هستیم و تصمیم گرفته‌ایم که منتظر بمانیم تا بفهمیم چه چیزی خواهیم داشت. بچه‌ها واقعاً شگفت‌انگیزند، درست نیست؟

اوه، این بوقلمون و موقعیت هایی که عصبی کننده است خیلی جالب است. حالا من خیلی خوب متوجه شدم.

کارهای پاره وقت ها ها ها، واااای که خیلی زیاد نیاز دارند. به عنوان والدین، می‌خواهیم اطمینان حاصل کنیم که آنها بهترین زندگی ممکن را داشته باشند.

column3:
'I work as a freight driver and find that loads of us have them.....' 
'I sell insurance, so I get to work from home a lot. I am a homebody that likes to sit on the couch and watch TV.'

'Have your employers been accepting of your tats, when they do see you at an office ? '
'Oh yes, but I do cover them up as much as I can when I go into the office. Working at home helps me with that situation also.'

"Shame to cover them, luckily I don't have to. WHy Japanese influenced ?"
'I love the artwork and creativity.'

'It is very unique and beautiful for sure. As a woman I appreciate that style !'
'What are your tattoos of, origin or reasons?'

'Well, my first one was the hand print of my daughter as a baby, then I had three more children so had to add them. One led to another....'
'I want to add one for my son soon, I love the silhouette ones of mother and child.'

I have one of the dogs since I was 16. I rescued the other dog and cat after I finished college.
Rescues are always great! I have one rescue cat

Oh yes, they are my little friends and we live in our own little fantasy world. Just us. Haha.
Sounds cozy. I usually prefer to hang out with animals over people as well. :) Do the dogs and cat get along well?

Oh, they are best friends. I made sure when I adopted them they were okay around each other. My other dog eventually warmed up to them.
I am a little worried because my cats are pretty content with no other animals around. They've never been around dogs, so not sure how they'll react to a puppy

I think they will eventually warm up to them. You may have to get 2 dogs so they can play with each other and won't bother the cats.
Oh man. I haven't had a dog since I was a teenager, so I'm nervous enough about getting one. Cats seem easier.

I agree cats are so much easier, especially when it comes to potty training them. I don't miss that nightmare at all.
That's what I really dread. Mid-night wake ups to go out

من تعداد زیادی دوست ندارم، بنابراین بسیاری از وقت خود را با دو سگ و گربه‌ام می‌گذرانم.

من یکی از سگ‌ها را از وقتی ۱۶ ساله بودم دارم. سگ و گربه دیگر را پس از فارغ‌التحصیلی نجات دادم.

آره، آن‌ها دوستان کوچک من هستند و ما در دنیای فانتزی کوچک خود زندگی می‌کنیم. فقط ما. هاها.

اوه، آن‌ها بهترین دوستان هستند. من اطمینان حاصل کردم که زمانی که آن‌ها را پذیرفتم، اطراف هم خوب بودند. سگ دیگر من در نهایت با آن‌ها دوست شد.

فکر می‌کنم سرانجام به آنها گرم می‌شوند. شاید باید ۲ سگ بگیری تا با هم بازی کنند و گربه‌ها را ناراحت نکنند.

موافقم که گربه‌ها خیلی راحت‌ترند، به ویژه وقتی به آموزش دستشوییشان می‌رسد. اصلا از آن کابوس خاطره‌ای ندارم.

'I have 2 golden retrievers. What type of dogs do you have?'
'I have a Husky and a maltese Shiz Tzu. They are my little babies!'
'Aww, I bet they are gorgeous! My parents love my pets too and treat them like grandkids. haha.'
'Mine too! They are definitely loved and treated like our kids by the whole family. How long have you had your babies?'
'I have had mine for 3 years? Do you enjoy dressing them up for Halloween?'
'Oh yes! This year they will be dressed up as Count Dracula and Mrs. Dracula. I cant wait! do you dress them up on halloween?'
'I dressed mine up as clowns last years as a tribute to my father and grandfather who worked for a circus! Fun theme.'
'How fun! I am thinking about dressing up as a bat to match my babies Dracula theme!'
'Aww, that is a great idea. I am still thinking about this year. There are so many ideas that I love. Any suggestons?'
'Not really, there are cute ideas on the internet. I would try looking there'
'That is a great idea. I would like maybe a zombie theme.'
'That reminds me of the video game called Zombies Ate My Neighbors. do you know the game?'

column3:
What other foods do you like?  
Oh, I like all foods, just vegetables most of all.  I do love Cheetos, though.  
Cheetos are good!  I'm not a big fan of vegetables.  If I had to choose, I would say green beans are my favorite.  
I like green beans, too.  Especially when they're just picked.  How do you like to cook them?

I like them best baked or using the air fryer.  Have you every used an air fryer? 
No, but I'm interested in them.  Are they really healthier than deep frying?
I think the food tastes just as good if not better.  They have to be healthier, since no oil is used.  
That makes sense =)  I want to eat healthy, but do indulge in fried food sometimes - this could help that.

Yes it could.  I love using mine.  I have cooked many meals in it.  Pork chops are my favorite in the air fryer.  
Oh wow, that sounds SO good.  I wonder if I could make fries out of carrots in it...?  Dip 'em in ranch ;)
it might work. I've never tried that. I have put green beans in there and they are somewhat crispy. Never as good as the french fry 
Yeah, french fries are hard to beat.  I think I'd try a lot of different fresh veggies in it, see which ones crisped up the best.

شما چه غذاهای دیگری را دوست دارید؟

چیتوس خوبند! من طرفدار بزرگی از سبزیجات نیستم. اگر باید انتخاب کنم، می‌گویم لوبیا سبز مورد علاقه من است.

من بهترین آن‌ها را پخته یا با استفاده از فریزر هوایی دوست دارم. آیا تا به حال از فریزر هوایی استفاده کرده‌اید؟

فکر می‌کنم غذا همانند یا بهتر از قبل خوشمزه است. آن‌ها باید سالم‌تر باشند، زیرا هیچ روغنی استفاده نمی‌شود.

بله ممکن است. من دوست دارم از خودم استفاده کنم. من برای زیادی غذا در آن پخته ام. کتف گوشت خوک مورد علاقه من در فرایر است.

ممکن است کار کند. من هرگز این کار را امتحان نکرده‌ام. من لوبیای سبز را در آن قرار داده‌ام و آنها کمی خرد و خشک هستند. هرگز به اندازه سیب‌زمینی سرخ شده خوب نیستند.

I haven't really tried listening to any. Call me old school but I like having the physical book in hand. Maybe look up something to do with country music? Lots of people do prefer hardcopy bound books, nothing wrong with that. I dislike driving, so it's a good safe distraction for me to have something to listen to
It is a safe distraction alright! I'm 23 and still haven't got my license yet. It gets pretty hard getting around in Tennessee. Oh I bet. How do you get around? You must live in a downtown area with lots to do within walking distance?
Yeah, living downtown gets pretty expensive! I usually take taxis if I need to go around. I hate public transit. It must be nice to have so many conveniences close by though. I live in a rural area, and while I enjoy the quiet, we can't even get restaurant delivery

بله، حداقل موسیقی اون هنوز برای ما برای گوش دادن باقی می‌ماند! درسته، درسته. افسانه‌های بزرگ واقعاً هرگز مرده نمی‌شوند! آیا شما بیشتر موسیقی قدیمی کانتری را دوست دارید یا موسیقی جدیدتر؟

در حال حاضر چه کتاب‌های صوتی را گوش می‌دهید؟ من همین الان کتاب "آموزش: یادداشت‌های زندگی" را تمام کردم و در حال تصمیم‌گیری برای گوش دادن به چه کتابی بعدی هستم. آیا شما از کتاب‌های صوتی خوشتان می‌آید؟

این یک حواس پرتی امن است! من ۲۳ ساله هستم و هنوز گواهینامه رانندگی خود را دریافت نکرده‌ام. در تنسی انتقال دادن خیلی سخت است. اوه حتما. چطور انتقال می‌یابید؟ شما حتما در منطقه وسط شهر زندگی می‌کنید که فعالیت‌های زیادی در فاصله قدم زدن دارد؟

من از چیزهای قدیمی خوشم می‌آید، چارلی دنیلز یکی از هنرمندان مورد علاقه من است. شما چطور؟ من عاشق موسیقی کشوری قدیمی و غمگین هستم، مرل هگارد، ویلون جنینگز. اما از موسیقی‌های امروزی خبری ندارم. معمولاً در ماشین پادکست‌ها یا کتاب‌های صوتی گوش می‌دهم.

من واقعاً تلاش نکردم که به هیچ کدام گوش کنم. به من بگو که قدیمی هستم اما من دوست دارم کتاب فیزیکی در دست داشته باشم. شاید چیزی مربوط به موسیقی کانتری بگردی؟ خیلی از مردم ترجیح می‌دهند کتاب‌های جلد سخت داشته باشند، هیچ مشکلی در این وجود ندارد. من از رانندگی نفرت دارم، بنابراین یک حواس‌پرتی ایمن خوب برای من است که چیزی برای گوش دادن داشته باشم.

بله، زندگی در مرکز شهر خیلی گران است! معمولاً اگر نیاز به رفت و آمد دارم تاکسی می‌گیرم. من از حمل و نقل عمومی بدم می‌آید. اما حتماً خوب است که اینقدر امکانات نزدیک دسترسی دارید. من در منطقه روستایی زندگی می‌کنم و اگرچه از آرامش لذت می‌برم، حتی نمی‌توانیم غذا از رستوران تحویل بگیریم.

"It was strange, I could eat them, but I couldn't be anywhere near them while they were cooking.  do you have any quirks like that?"
"I haven't had any problems with foods, but pollen has always bothered."
'Had to go with hubby to work brunch, eggs cooking and I had to hide in bathroom. Have you ever had to stop because of pollen'
"I've never had to stop anything because of pollen, but allergy season is always tough."
"Do you have to take medicine for it" 
"I don't but I probably should. I just tough it out."
"Where do you work?"
'I work at a restaurant in the city. What about you?'
"Glad you don't have to work outside with allergies!  I tutor kids in math.  No cooking for me!"
"I've always been bad with math! How do you like tutoring?"
" love it, it's really rewarding. I am going to school to be an engineer, there just isn't a lot of time. I wish I could live forever!"
'Me too! More time in the day would be nice too.'
